sequenceDiagram
    participant CO as Compliance Officer
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant IT as IT Ops

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Request intake documentation & identity pre-screening
    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    Note over C,S: 📄 DOC-1: Request Intake Record<br/>(timestamp, customer ID, channel)
    S->>CO: Identity pre-screening request
    CO->>CO: Identity Pre-Screening<br/>(KYC/AML checks, sanctions list)
    Note over CO: RACI – Identity Pre-Screening<br/>R: Compliance Officer<br/>A: Compliance Officer<br/>C: Sales Team<br/>I: Finance
    CO-->>S: Identity pre-screening cleared
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    S->>F: Credit check request

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Risk assessment with compliance validation & documentation
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Co., Clean History?)
    Note over F: 📄 DOC-2: Risk Assessment Record<br/>(score, criteria, data sources, timestamp)
    F->>CO: Risk scoring output for validation
    CO->>CO: Validate Risk Scoring Output<br/>(methodology review, data integrity check)
    Note over CO: RACI – Risk Score Validation<br/>R: Compliance Officer<br/>A: Compliance Officer<br/>C: Finance<br/>I: Sales Team
    CO-->>F: Risk scoring validated

    alt Low-Risk (all criteria met) - Expedited Path
        Note over F,S: RACI – Auto-Approval Decision<br/>R: Finance<br/>A: Finance<br/>C: Compliance Officer<br/>I: Sales Team, IT Ops
        F-->>S: Auto-approved (low-risk bypass)
        Note over F,S: 📄 DOC-3: Approval Justification<br/>(auto-approve rationale, risk score, policy ref)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited)
        IT->>CO: Access control review request
        CO->>CO: Access Control Review<br/>(least-privilege check, role assignment audit)
        Note over CO: RACI – Access Control Review<br/>R: Compliance Officer<br/>A: Compliance Officer<br/>C: IT Ops<br/>I: Sales Team
        CO-->>IT: Access control approved
        Note over IT,CO: 📄 DOC-4: Audit Log<br/>(provisioned resources, permissions, reviewer, timestamp)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk - Standard Path
        F->>F: Route to Finance Director for approval
        Note over F: RACI – Finance Director Approval<br/>R: Finance Director<br/>A: Finance<br/>C: Compliance Officer<br/>I: Sales Team
        F-->>S: Finance Director Approval (24h SLA)
        Note over F,S: 📄 DOC-3: Approval Justification<br/>(director sign-off, conditions, risk factors)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
        IT->>CO: Access control review request
        CO->>CO: Access Control Review<br/>(least-privilege check, role assignment audit)
        Note over CO: RACI – Access Control Review<br/>R: Compliance Officer<br/>A: Compliance Officer<br/>C: IT Ops<br/>I: Sales Team
        CO-->>IT: Access control approved
        Note over IT,CO: 📄 DOC-4: Audit Log<br/>(provisioned resources, permissions, reviewer, timestamp)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    end
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Closure documentation
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled
    Note over S,CO: 📄 DOC-5: Closure Record<br/>(onboarding summary, all checkpoint sign-offs,<br/>compliance attestation, final timestamp)
    S->>CO: Closure attestation request
    CO-->>S: SOX compliance attestation confirmed
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added Compliance Officer as a new participant at the top of the diagram. Introduced three compliance checkpoints: (1) Identity Pre-Screening before the credit check with KYC/AML verification, (2) Risk Scoring Validation after Finance completes the risk assessment but before the routing decision, and (3) Access Control Review after account provisioning in both the expedited and standard paths. Five documentation gates are attached as Notes (not inline flow-blocking nodes): DOC-1 at request intake, DOC-2 at risk assessment output, DOC-3 at approval justification (in both alt branches), DOC-4 as audit logs after provisioning (both branches), and DOC-5 as a closure record after kickoff scheduling. Every major decision point carries a RACI annotation identifying Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, and Informed parties. All original business logic including the risk-based alt/else routing, expedited path, and post-provisioning steps remains completely intact.